wlist.json` — `{ \"fingerprints\": [\"...\"] }`. Add `loadAllowlist(repo)` / `addToAllowlist(repo, fps)` in scan.ts. Findings with allowlisted fingerprints are suppressed.\n\n**Sync gate** in src/store.ts `sync()`: before the push phase (both \"both\" and \"push\" modes), unless the caller passes a new option `skipScan: true` or config `scan.tier === \"off\"`:\n1. Determine which local events the remote does not have: `git ls-remote <remote> refs/notes/conversation-ledger`; if the ref exists remotely, fetch it to a temp ref, read all its events' ids, and scan only local events (all anchors + pending) whose ids are absent remotely; if no remote ref, scan everything. Clean up the temp ref.\n2. Tier: \"standard\" by default, \"paranoid\" if config says so or option `paranoid: true`.\n3. If findings remain after allowlist filtering: print a report to stderr (one finding per line: short event id, conversation, timestamp, rule, excerpt, fingerprint) followed by remediation instructions naming `cledger redact <event-id>`, `cledger allow <fingerprint>`, and `cledger sync --no-scan`, then throw an Error so the push does not happen (fetch/merge phase may still have completed — that's fine and should be reported).\nChange sync's signature compatibly: `sync(repo, remote, mode, opts?: { skipScan?: boolean; paranoid?: boolean })` — keep existing tests passing.\n\n**CLI**: `cledger scan [--all|--rev R] [--paranoid]` — scans local events (default: everything including pending; `--rev` restricts by reachability), prints findings, exits 1 if any (CI-friendly), 0 otherwise. `cledger allow <fingerprint...>` appends to the allowlist. `cledger sync` gains `--no-scan` and `--paranoid` flags. Update the USAGE string for all of these (and for `redact` below).\n\n## Part 2: cledger redact + local purge\n\n**src/store.ts** (or a new src/redact/purge.ts if cleaner): \n```ts\nexport async function redactEvent(repo: RepoInfo, idPrefix: string, opts: { pattern?: string; all?: boolean; reason?: string }): Promise<{ event: EvidenceEvent; redactionEvent: EvidenceEvent; squashed: boolean }>;\n```\n1. Locate the event by id prefix across all anchors and pending.jsonl; error if not found or ambiguous.\n2. Rewrite it: with `--pattern`, compile the regex and apply it as a rule with id `manual` to content + raw.data (same placeholder/fingerprint scheme via redactText/redactDraft machinery); with `--all`, replace `content` with the string `[REDACTED:manual:<fp>]` (fp of the canonical original content) and delete `raw`. Require exactly one of --pattern/--all. Append the new records to the event's existing `redactions` array.\n3. **CRITICAL — id preservation**: the rewritten event KEEPS its original `id`. If the id were recomputed, a later transcript rescan would regenerate the original unredacted event under the old id, and dedup would no longer catch it — the secret would silently return. The companion redaction event attests why the content hash no longer matches the id. Write a comment in the code explaining exactly this, and a test proving it (see below).\n4. Append a companion event: kind `\"redaction\"`, actor from git identity (see how src/adapters/claude-code.ts uses gitUserIdentity), producer tool `\"cledger\"`, occurred_at now, content `{ target: <original id>, mode: \"pattern\"|\"all\", fingerprints: [...], reason? }`, links `[{ rel: \"redacts\", target: <original id> }]`, same conversation ref as the target (same seq is fine — sortEvents tiebreaks). This goes through normal appendEvents.\n5. **Local purge (squash)**: after rewriting, check `git ls-remote <remote(s)> refs/notes/conversation-ledger` (just \"origin\" is fine for v1; treat ls-remote failure — e.g. no remote — as \"no remote ref\"). If the remote does NOT have the ref: squash the local notes history — `git rev-parse refs/notes/conversation-ledger^{tree}`, `git commit-tree <tree> -m \"cledger: notes history squashed after redaction\"` with NO parent, `git update-ref refs/notes/conversation-ledger <new-sha>` — so the pre-redaction blob becomes unreachable. If the remote DOES have the ref: skip the squash and print a clear warning that already-shared history still contains the prior content and post-push purge is separate future tooling. Return `squashed` accordingly.\n6. Handle the pending-queue case (event not yet anchored): rewrite the line in pending.jsonl; no squash needed.\n\n**CLI**: `cledger redact <event-id-prefix> (--pattern REGEX | --all) [--reason TEXT]` — prints what was redacted (rule/fingerprints), the companion event id, and whether history was squashed.\n\n## Tests (src/test/scan.test.ts, src/test/redact-command.test.ts)\n\nFollow helpers.ts fixture patterns; store-sync.test.ts shows how to set up a bare remote. Cover at minimum:\n- scanEvents: standard tier finds a `password=...` in content and in raw; excerpt never contains the full secret; allowlisted fingerprint suppressed; paranoid finds a high-entropy token that standard does not; pure-hex and `[REDACTED:` candidates skipped.\n- sync gate: repo with bare remote; event containing `password=supersecret123` → sync throws, nothing pushed (assert remote ref state), report names the fingerprint; after `addToAllowlist` sync succeeds; `skipScan: true` bypasses; already-pushed events are NOT rescanned (push an event, then add a new clean one — no findings from the old one even if it would match).\n- redactEvent: append an event with a secret the capture tier misses (e.g. `db_password: hunter2xK9aa`); redact with --pattern; note line rewritten (secret gone from content AND raw), original id preserved (assert equal), companion redaction event present with links.redacts; **the dedup test**: re-append the original unredacted draft → it dedups (0 appended) because the id is preserved; squash happened when no remote ref exists (assert `git log refs/notes/conversation-ledger` shows exactly 1 commit and the old note blob content is absent from `git cat-file` reachability — checking commit count is suff