never available.\n- Keep storage out of ordinary working-tree status views while retaining normal\n  Git durability and shareability.\n- Make sharing, retention, redaction, and deletion deliberate user choices.\n\n## Non-goals for the foundation\n\n- Deciding which historical statement is correct or intended.\n- Summarizing, ranking, embedding, or otherwise interpreting conversations.\n- Controlling an agent, enforcing a workflow, or orchestrating agents.\n- Capturing reasoning the provider hides (visible reasoning is recorded when\n  exposed), or claiming it can reproduce a native agent session.\n\nThose belong to clients such as Turnbridge and Intent Recall, not to this core\nstorage layer.\n","filePath":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger/docs/PRODUCT_INTENT.md","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37},"type":"text"},"type":"user","userType":"external","uuid":"99e2e244-09dd-45a6-a432-ef4ff97dd91c","version":"2.1.215"},"format":"claude-code-jsonl/1"},"recorded_at":"2026-07-20T01:54:00.054Z","schema":"conversation-ledger/v1"}
{"actor":{"type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1\t# Product intent\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tTurnbridge lets a developer continue a visible coding conversation in a\n6\tdifferent agent CLI when they choose to switch providers or tools. It retains\n7\tthe full user-visible turn history—messages, tool calls, and tool results—\n8\trather than requiring a last-minute summary from a rate-limited model.\n9\t\n10\tIt serves two users who are often the same person on different days: a solo\n11\tdeveloper hopping CLIs mid-task (rate limits, model choice), and small\n12\tcollaborating groups whose members use *different* CLIs and want to pick up\n13\teach other's conversations. Sharing rides on Conversation Ledger's git-notes\n14\tstorage; each turn is attributed to its human author via the repo's git\n15\tidentity, and listings show only your own (plus unattributed) conversations\n16\tunless you ask for everyone's.\n17\t\n18\t## Behavioral commitments\n19\t\n20\t- Capture every available visible turn incrementally, not only on clean exit\n21\t  (delivered by Conversation Ledger's hooks; see division below).\n22\t- Preserve source content faithfully and label its originating CLI.\n23\t- Offer one resume picker across supported CLIs while making the session type\n24\t  honest: native resume for same-CLI records, native-format fabrication for\n25\t  cross-CLI records, transcript rehydration as the always-available fallback.\n26\t- Prefer conversations whose repository and code state match the current work;\n27\t  warn rather than silently treating mismatched history as current.\n28\t- Never claim to transfer hidden reasoning, private provider state, or an\n29\t  exact native session; a fabricated session is labeled as imported.\n30\t- Put the developer in control of capture, sharing, and deletion. Sharing is\n31\t  explicit (`cledger sync`); listings default to the current user's records.\n32\t\n33\t## Non-goals\n34\t\n35\t- A team presence system, task tracker, or agent orchestration framework.\n36\t- Inferring or replacing human intent.\n37\t- Summarized \"handoff notes\" (sticky-note-style); Turnbridge moves the literal\n38\t  record.\n39\t\n40\t## Relationship to Conversation Ledger\n41\t\n42\tTurnbridge is a client of Conversation Ledger, which owns the durable neutral\n43\trecord **and** the source-CLI capture adapters (hooks, transcript parsers,\n44\tcursors, dedup). Turnbridge owns everything on the resume side: the unified\n45\tpicker, ownership/compatibility filtering, target-CLI session fabrication,\n46\tbootstrap rehydration, and the optional command shims.\n47\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_0123VdAejxxh6eqwk2AftYLW","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"c08f650fedfb44dd1e095b61aa2bd43ed5735597","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:353eecbb-eaf7-4854-a575-a9d56e290707","seq":125},"id":"ev1-d9cb3d91d6bbb91cb17f52f178fa62fafb774b5ca05d5e2b50d7b913c044ba4b","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T02:37:41.729Z","producer":{"session_id":"353eecbb-eaf7-4854-a575-a9d56e290707","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.2.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"content":"1\t# Product intent\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tTurnbridge lets a developer continue a visible coding conversation in a\n6\tdifferent agent CLI when they choose to switch providers or tools. It retains\n7\tthe full user-visible turn history—messages, tool calls, and tool results—\n8\trather than requiring a last-minute summary from a rate-limited model.\n9\t\n10\tIt serves two users who are often the same person on different days: a solo\n11\tdeveloper hopping CLIs mid-task (rate limits, model choice), and small\n12\tcollaborating groups whose members use *